# =============================================================================
# LDIF Test Data — Access Drift Visualization Scenarios
# Apply with: ldapmodify -x -D "cn=admin,dc=acmecorp,dc=com" -w <password> -f testdata/acmecorp-drift-test.ldif
#
# This LDIF:
# 1. Adds 'department' attribute to users (needed for peer-group analysis)
# 2. Creates drift-specific access groups
# 3. Adds anomalous group memberships to create detectable drift outliers
#
# Expected drift findings after analysis:
# - Engineering: 3 outliers with Finance/HR access (Payroll-Admin, HR-DataAdmin, DataAccess-Financial)
# - Finance: 2 outliers with Engineering access (Code-Deploy-Prod, AWS-Developers)
# - Sales: 2 outliers with sensitive data access (DataAccess-PII, DataAccess-Financial)
# - HR: 1 outlier with production access (Code-Deploy-Prod, AWS-Developers)
# =============================================================================

# ─── Step 1: Add department attribute to users ────────────────────────────────
# (needed because the peer group analysis groups by 'department')
# We add it to a representative sample from each department.

# --- Engineering users (20 users) ---
