# ─── Step 2: Create drift-specific access groups ──────────────────────────────
# These groups represent typical per-department access patterns.
# Most department members should be in the groups typical for their role.
# A few outliers will be added to groups outside their department norm.

# Engineering-typical groups: GitHub-Users, AWS-Developers, BuildSystem-Users, Jira-Users
# Finance-typical groups: DataAccess-Financial, Jira-Users, Confluence-Users
# Sales-typical groups: Jira-Users, Slack-Users, Confluence-Users
# HR-typical groups: DataAccess-PII, HR-DataAdmin, Jira-Users

# ─── Step 3: Add members to groups to create drift patterns ──────────────────

# --- Add ALL Engineering users to their expected groups ---
# GitHub-Users: all 20 engineering users (100% peer membership)
dn: cn=GitHub-Users,ou=Access,ou=Groups,dc=acmecorp,dc=com
changetype: modify
